const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Perlick worth the premium price for bar use?",
    a: "For high-volume bar and hospitality use, yes. Perlick has 7 to 12 year typical service life vs 5 to 8 for mid-tier brands in the same environment. The lifetime construction (stainless cabinet, premium gaskets, self-closing hinges) reduces service intervals significantly. For low-volume use (small office, residential bar), mid-tier brands (Beverage-Air UCR, True TUC) make more financial sense."
  },
  {
    q: "Why does my undercounter run warmer than the spec?",
    a: "Most common cause: tight installation with restricted airflow. Compact units need 2 inches clearance on sides and back for proper condensing unit airflow. If the unit is jammed against cabinetry, the condenser can't cool, the compressor short-cycles, and internal temp climbs. We pull the unit forward, verify clearance, and often that fixes the issue without parts."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Perlick HP15, HP24, and BBR series?",
    a: "Yes. Perlick is our most common premium undercounter brand. We have Perlick parts network access for OEM components, including drawer slides for HP24 drawer-style configurations, self-closing hinge kits, and BBR back-bar glass-door anti-condensation heaters."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you come out at 2 AM after the bar closes?",
    a: "Phones answered 24/7. Scheduled dispatch starts 8 AM Mon-Sat. For after-hours emergency dispatch (1 to 7 AM specifically for bar post-close service), call ahead to confirm tech availability. Usually possible with notice."
  },
  {
    q: "My food truck refrigerator keeps failing. Why?",
    a: "Food trucks compress equipment service life because of: (1) constant vibration during driving, (2) frequent ambient temp swings (parking lot 110°F to operation 75°F to off-hours 60°F), (3) limited clearance for condensing unit airflow, (4) coastal and dust exposure depending on event locations. Plan annual preventive service at minimum, often semi-annual for high-use operations."
  },
  {
    q: "My undercounter uses R-290. What's that?",
    a: "R-290 is propane, a hydrocarbon refrigerant used in newer green commercial undercounters (post-2020 Perlick, True, others). Different service procedures than R-134a. Requires R-290 certification beyond standard EPA 608. We have it."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days parts and labor on every repair. BHGS #A49573 and BBB A+. EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410) plus R-290 certified for newer green-refrigerant units."
  }
];

