        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts and labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 07 WHY US -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Why bars and operations call us</p>
    <h2>What separates our undercounter service from general commercial refrigeration.</h2>

    <ul class="reasons-list">
      <li><strong>Perlick expertise.</strong> Wisconsin parts network, Perlick service patterns, drawer-style HP24 specialty knowledge.</li>
      <li><strong>EPA 608 Universal plus R-290 certification.</strong> Green refrigerant on newer Perlick and True undercounters requires R-290 specific certification beyond standard EPA 608.</li>
      <li><strong>Bar splash awareness.</strong> We know the failure patterns specific to bar environments: sticky residue, splash damage, frequent door cycling.</li>
      <li><strong>Coastal salt expertise.</strong> Marina del Rey, Manhattan Beach, Newport Beach: 30% of our undercounter work.</li>
      <li><strong>24/7 phone answering, no emergency surcharge.</strong> Bars often need post-close service (1 to 3 AM after last call).</li>
      <li><strong>Food truck service.</strong> Mobile units welcomed, dispatch flexibility for food truck schedules.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus BBB A+ verifiable.</strong></li>
